{"key":"post-12436921","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>12436921</id>\n<content>A four hour or greater soak is fine, but don't go over 24.&amp;nbsp; Disregard bad advice above not to boil.&amp;nbsp; I bring grains to a &lt;b&gt;rapid boil&lt;/b&gt; for ten minutes.&amp;nbsp; It's important to start the grains in cold water and then bring to a boil.&amp;nbsp;  NEVER bring water to a boil and dump your grains in.&amp;nbsp; That will lead to burst kernels and release of starch.&amp;nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>12436993</next>\n<prev>12435397</prev>\n<first>12435104</first>\n<last>12934711</last>\n<when>1271953144</when>\n<utime>04/22/10 07:19 PM</utime>\n</post>"}